    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document describes common misinterpretations and some ambiguities in the Signaling Compression Protocol (SigComp), and offers guidance to developers to resolve any resultant problems.  SigComp defines a scheme for compressing messages generated by application protocols such as the Session Initiation Protocol (SIP).  This document updates the following RFCs: RFC 3320, RFC 3321, and RFC 3485. [STANDARDS-TRACK]&lt;/p&gt;</t>
